snippet.textDisplay:
Ok... I will not do the mistake of comparing this version with the original one. Upon listening this version I think the bass guitar was overpowering the vocals. Both singers are extremely talented and I always enjoy their vocals. BUT here I will have to put efforts in listening them coz the guitar was keep on suppressing them. 

Also, I felt the rhytm of the guitar was different from the rythm of the song/vocals. Though I thoroughly enjoyed the 'jugalbandi' of bass guitar and saxaphone (with female vocal) at 4:33. it felt like an original piece of its own and guitar's rythm (1-2, 1-2-3-4) worked so well. But the mixing it with the lyrics of the song didn't work for me. 

But still a praise worthy effort.
